From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: FMan HM node install (productive, M3-3c)

Forward-port of the FMan Header-Manipulation (HM) ordered-op-list silicon
programming path into the COMMON board patch stack (built-in for
default/vpp/ask via the FSL_FMAN_PCD config from patch 0092).  Re-anchors
the tested ask20 HMCT/HMTD MURAM-encoding path (ask20 branch patches 0014
body-1 + 0015 body-2) onto the 0092 PCD subsystem + 0097 KeyGen + 0098 CC
base, adapted to the dpaa1 flat-C HM op set declared by board patch 0090a.
This is PR4 of the dpaa1 PCD forward-port closing M3-3c.

What this adds
--------------
- fman_pcd_manip.c (new, fsl_dpaa_fman.ko): the productive HM installer.
  Defines struct fman_pcd_hm_node and four static per-op HMCT encoders
  (vlan_insert / vlan_strip / mpls_push / mpls_pop).  fman_pcd_hm_install()
  allocates a 16-byte HMTD + 128-byte HMCT MURAM region, walks the neutral
  op list emitting a real FMan generic INSRT/RMV command word (+ inline
  4-byte payload for the insert ops) per LS1046A RM 8.7.5, stamps HMCD_LAST
  on the last word, finalises the HMTD (cfg=TYPE|EXT_HMCT, hmcdBasePtr,
  opCode=HMAN_OC=0x35), publishes the node on pcd->manip_list, and returns
  the HMTD MURAM byte offset as the opaque handle (the value a CC action's
  hm_handle carries).  fman_pcd_hm_destroy() is idempotent: it finds the
  node by handle+port_id, zeroes the HMTD opCode, and frees the MURAM.
  The MURAM internals (fman_pcd_muram_alloc / fman_muram_offset_to_vbase,
  the latter NOT EXPORT_SYMBOL'd) stay inside this module - the 0097/0098
  bridge idiom.  Per operator decision 2026-05-29 (spec sec 6 item 6) the
  L2/VLAN/MPLS rewrites use the durable in-tree generic INSRT/RMV primitive,
  NOT the ask20 0058/0065 HMD/graft shortcut.

- include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h: publishes the neutral, big-endian-ready
  descriptor struct fman_pcd_hm_hw_{op,spec} + enum fman_pcd_hm_hw_op_type
  + FMAN_PCD_HM_HW_MAX_OPS, plus the two install/destroy prototypes.  The
  neutral struct lives in the public header so both fsl_dpa.ko (which owns
  the host-endian struct fman_hm_spec in dpaa_fman_caps.h) and
  fsl_dpaa_fman.ko can see it without a circular include.

- dpaa_fman_caps.c (fsl_dpa.ko): makes fman_hm_node_install() /
  fman_hm_node_destroy() productive.  install() gates on FMAN_CAP_HM_NODES
  (BIT1) BEFORE touching MURAM (spec sec 3.5), translates the host-endian
  struct fman_hm_spec into the neutral fman_pcd_hm_hw_spec
  (dpaa_hm_spec_to_hw(): VLAN tpid->tpid_be / vlan_id->vid / pcp->pcp, MPLS
  name-for-name; VLAN_STRIP/MPLS_POP carry no params), resolves the PCD via
  fman_get_pcd(fm), and delegates to fman_pcd_hm_install().  destroy() gates
  on caps and delegates to the idempotent fman_pcd_hm_destroy().  Adds
  #include <linux/slab.h> for kzalloc/kfree.

- Makefile: adds fman_pcd_manip.o to the FSL_FMAN_PCD object list.

Endianness note
---------------
The neutral HM fields carry HOST values (unlike the CC neutral key, whose
multi-byte fields are pre-swapped to FMan-BE in dpaa_cc_key_to_hw()).  The
HM encoder assembles each inline payload word in host order and writes it
via iowrite32be, which performs the host->BE swap on the whole assembled
word.  The "_be" suffix on fman_pcd_hm_hw_op.vlan_insert.tpid_be is thus a
slight misnomer kept for symmetry with the CC descriptor; it holds the host
TPID (e.g. 0x8100).

Verified: native arm64 compile of drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/ and
.../dpaa/ with LOCALVERSION=-vyos is 0 warnings / 0 errors; fman_pcd_manip.o,
dpaa_fman_caps.o and both built-in.a archives build clean.

Spec sec 5.5.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
index 686d2f0..e366e85 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
@@ -19,6 +19,7 @@
 #include <linux/module.h>
 #include <linux/moduleparam.h>
 #include <linux/printk.h>
+#include <linux/slab.h>
 #include <linux/types.h>
 
 #include <linux/of.h>
@@ -331,19 +332,110 @@ EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_cc_tree_destroy);
  * downstream caller. Spec sec 5.5.
  * ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
 
+/*
+ * Translate the host-endian ordered-op list (struct fman_hm_spec, private
+ * to fsl_dpa.ko) into the neutral struct fman_pcd_hm_hw_spec the fman-side
+ * installer consumes.  The neutral HM fields carry HOST values (the encoder
+ * in fman_pcd_manip.c assembles the inline payload word and writes it
+ * big-endian via iowrite32be), so this is a one-to-one field copy: VLAN
+ * tpid->tpid_be, vlan_id->vid, pcp->pcp; MPLS name-for-name.  VLAN_STRIP /
+ * MPLS_POP carry no params.
+ */
+static void dpaa_hm_spec_to_hw(const struct fman_hm_spec *spec,
+			      struct fman_pcd_hm_hw_spec *hw)
+{
+	u8 i;
+
+	memset(hw, 0, sizeof(*hw));
+	hw->num_ops = spec->num_ops;
+
+	for (i = 0; i < spec->num_ops; i++) {
+		const struct fman_hm_op *src = &spec->ops[i];
+		struct fman_pcd_hm_hw_op *dst = &hw->ops[i];
+
+		switch (src->type) {
+		case FMAN_HM_OP_VLAN_STRIP:
+			dst->type = FMAN_PCD_HM_HW_OP_VLAN_STRIP;
+			break;
+		case FMAN_HM_OP_VLAN_INSERT:
+			dst->type = FMAN_PCD_HM_HW_OP_VLAN_INSERT;
+			dst->vlan_insert.tpid_be = src->vlan_insert.tpid;
+			dst->vlan_insert.vid = src->vlan_insert.vlan_id;
+			dst->vlan_insert.pcp = src->vlan_insert.pcp;
+			break;
+		case FMAN_HM_OP_MPLS_PUSH:
+			dst->type = FMAN_PCD_HM_HW_OP_MPLS_PUSH;
+			dst->mpls_push.label = src->mpls_push.label;
+			dst->mpls_push.tc = src->mpls_push.tc;
+			dst->mpls_push.s = src->mpls_push.s;
+			dst->mpls_push.ttl = src->mpls_push.ttl;
+			break;
+		case FMAN_HM_OP_MPLS_POP:
+			dst->type = FMAN_PCD_HM_HW_OP_MPLS_POP;
+			break;
+		}
+	}
+}
+
+/*
+ * Productive HM node install (spec sec 5.5).  Gates on FMAN_CAP_HM_NODES
+ * BEFORE touching MURAM per spec sec 3.5; on a board without it (mainline
+ * ucode 106) returns -ENOTSUPP so the flavor layer fails soft.  On the Mono
+ * Gateway DK the 210.10.1 QEF blob lights HM up (caps = 0x17), so this path
+ * is live there.  Translates the host-endian op list into the neutral
+ * fman-side descriptor and delegates the silicon programming to
+ * fman_pcd_hm_install() in fsl_dpaa_fman.ko (which owns the MURAM
+ * allocator).  On success *handle receives the HMTD MURAM byte offset, the
+ * value a CC action carries as hm_handle.
+ */
 int fman_hm_node_install(struct fman *fm, u8 port_id,
 			 const struct fman_hm_spec *spec, u32 *handle)
 {
-	if (!handle)
+	struct fman_pcd_hm_hw_spec *hw;
+	struct fman_pcd *pcd;
+	int err;
+
+	if (!fm || !spec || !handle)
 		return -EINVAL;
 	*handle = 0;
-	return -ENOTSUPP;
+	if (!fman_hm_caps_supported())
+		return -ENOTSUPP;
+	if (spec->num_ops == 0 || spec->num_ops > FMAN_HM_MAX_OPS)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	pcd = fman_get_pcd(fm);
+	if (!pcd)
+		return -ENXIO;
+
+	hw = kzalloc(sizeof(*hw), GFP_KERNEL);
+	if (!hw)
+		return -ENOMEM;
+
+	dpaa_hm_spec_to_hw(spec, hw);
+
+	err = fman_pcd_hm_install(pcd, port_id, hw, handle);
+	kfree(hw);
+	return err;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_hm_node_install);
 
+/*
+ * Productive HM node destroy (spec sec 5.5).  Gates on FMAN_CAP_HM_NODES,
+ * resolves the PCD and delegates to fman_pcd_hm_destroy(), which is
+ * idempotent (a handle matching no live node is a no-op).  Returns 0 on a
+ * board without HM caps (nothing was ever installed).
+ */
 int fman_hm_node_destroy(struct fman *fm, u8 port_id, u32 handle)
 {
-	/* idempotent no-op on stub; productive impl will validate handle */
+	struct fman_pcd *pcd;
+
+	if (!fm)
+		return 0;
+	if (!fman_hm_caps_supported())
+		return 0;
+	pcd = fman_get_pcd(fm);
+	if (pcd)
+		return fman_pcd_hm_destroy(pcd, port_id, handle);
 	return 0;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_hm_node_destroy);
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/Makefile b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/Makefile
index 912290f..1428ed4 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/Makefile
@@ -6,6 +6,6 @@ obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_FMAN) += fsl_dpaa_fman_port.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_FMAN) += fsl_dpaa_mac.o
 
 fsl_dpaa_fman-objs	:= fman_muram.o fman.o fman_sp.o fman_keygen.o
-fsl_dpaa_fman-$(CONFIG_FSL_FMAN_PCD) += fman_pcd.o fman_pcd_kg.o fman_pcd_cc.o
+fsl_dpaa_fman-$(CONFIG_FSL_FMAN_PCD) += fman_pcd.o fman_pcd_kg.o fman_pcd_cc.o fman_pcd_manip.o
 fsl_dpaa_fman_port-objs := fman_port.o
 fsl_dpaa_mac-objs:= mac.o fman_dtsec.o fman_memac.o fman_tgec.o
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..71060ee
--- /dev/null
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
@@ -0,0 +1,525 @@
+// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0
+/*
+ * FMan PCD Header Manipulation (HM) - ordered-op-list silicon programming.
+ *
+ * dpaa1 forward-port (PR4 of the PCD series closing M3-3c).  Re-anchors the
+ * tested ask20 HMCT/HMTD MURAM-encoding path (ask20 branch patches 0014
+ * body-1 + 0015 body-2) onto the 0092 PCD subsystem base, adapted to the
+ * dpaa1 HM op set declared by board patch 0090a:
+ *
+ *   enum fman_hm_op_type { VLAN_STRIP, VLAN_INSERT, MPLS_PUSH, MPLS_POP }
+ *
+ * The dpaa-side entry points (fman_hm_node_install / fman_hm_node_destroy in
+ * dpaa_fman_caps.c, fsl_dpa.ko) gate on FMAN_CAP_HM_NODES, translate their
+ * module-private host-endian struct fman_hm_spec into the neutral,
+ * already-big-endian-ready struct fman_pcd_hm_hw_spec declared in
+ * <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>, and delegate to the two EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL entry
+ * points below (which live here in fsl_dpaa_fman.ko alongside the MURAM
+ * allocator, so the silicon internals never cross the module boundary -
+ * identical bridge idiom to fman_pcd_cc.c / fman_pcd_kg.c).
+ *
+ * Authoritative reference
+ * -----------------------
+ * - LS1046A Reference Manual sec 8.7.5    (Header modification table).
+ * - LS1046A Reference Manual sec 8.7.5.4  (Auto checksum recompute).
+ * - LS1046A Reference Manual sec 8.7.4.3  (AD opcode-extension layout, used
+ *   by the CC MANIPULATE arm that carries the HMTD MURAM offset returned
+ *   from here as the CC action's hm_handle).
+ *
+ * Provenance
+ * ----------
+ * Mainline drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/ has zero manip code; the
+ * HMTD/HMCT layouts and command-word encodings below are authored from the
+ * RM, cross-referenced against the legacy NXP SDK fm_manip.{h,c} (read-only
+ * silicon-fact reference, no code copied).  The generic-insert/remove
+ * opcode path is the durable in-tree primitive chosen per operator decision
+ * 2026-05-29 (spec sec 6 item 6): the L2/VLAN/MPLS rewrites use a real FMan
+ * HMCT GENERIC_INSRT / GENERIC_RMV command, NOT the ask20 0058/0065 HMD
+ * graft shortcut.
+ */
+
+#include <linux/err.h>
+#include <linux/errno.h>
+#include <linux/export.h>
+#include <linux/io.h>
+#include <linux/kernel.h>
+#include <linux/list.h>
+#include <linux/module.h>
+#include <linux/mutex.h>
+#include <linux/slab.h>
+#include <linux/spinlock.h>
+#include <linux/types.h>
+
+#include <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>
+#include "fman.h"
+#include "fman_muram.h"
+#include "fman_pcd_internal.h"
+
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+/* HMTD (Header Manipulation Table Descriptor) layout - RM 8.7.5 p.2  */
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+
+/*
+ * The HMTD is a 16-byte MURAM-resident record consumed by the FMan
+ * header-manip engine.  Field offsets within the descriptor (all
+ * big-endian relative to the host):
+ *
+ *   0x0  u16 cfg          - HMTD configuration flags
+ *   0x4  u32 hmcdBasePtr  - HMCT base pointer (MURAM byte offset)
+ *   0xb  u8  opCode       - HMAN_OC family selector
+ *
+ * Cross-ref SDK fm_manip.h::t_Hmtd (packed struct).
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMTD_SIZE	16
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMTD_OFF_CFG	0x0
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMTD_OFF_HMCD_BASE	0x4
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMTD_OFF_OPCODE	0xb
+
+/*
+ * HMTD cfg-word bits (RM 8.7.5 + cross-ref SDK fm_manip.h::HMTD_CFG_*):
+ *   TYPE     - 0x4000, marks this descriptor as a header-manip
+ *   EXT_HMCT - 0x0080, HMCT lives outside the descriptor (always true
+ *              for our layout)
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMTD_CFG_TYPE	0x4000
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMTD_CFG_EXT_HMCT	0x0080
+
+/*
+ * HMAN_OC opcode family selectors (RM 8.7.5 + cross-ref SDK fm_manip.h
+ * HMAN_OC_IP_MANIP=0x34 / HMAN_OC=0x35).  The dpaa1 HM op set
+ * (VLAN/MPLS push/pop) is L2/L3-shim-only and never touches IP header
+ * fields, so every node uses the generic HMAN_OC family.
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMAN_OC	0x35
+
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+/* HMCT (Header Manipulation Command Table) layout - RM 8.7.5 p.4     */
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+
+/*
+ * HMCT is a sequence of 4-byte big-endian command words optionally
+ * followed by inline payload (also 4-byte aligned).  Each command word
+ * is encoded as:
+ *
+ *   bits[31:24]  opcode (HMCD_OP_*; cross-ref SDK fm_manip.h)
+ *   bits[23:0]   per-opcode operand bits
+ *
+ * The last command word OR's in HMCD_LAST=0x00800000 to terminate the
+ * list (silicon stops walking at the first word with that bit set).
+ *
+ * Sizing: worst case is FMAN_HM_MAX_OPS (8) ops, each a GENERIC_INSRT
+ * command word + 4-byte inline payload = 8 bytes per op = 64 bytes.
+ * Rounded up to 128 for slack.  gen_pool min_alloc_order=8 inside
+ * fman_muram_alloc() guarantees natural 256-byte alignment, stricter
+ * than every RM requirement.
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMCT_SIZE	128
+
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMCD_LAST	0x00800000u
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OC_SHIFT	24
+
+/* Generic insert/remove opcodes (RM 8.7.5 generic op encoding +
+ * cross-ref SDK fm_manip.h HMCD_OPCODE_GENERIC_INSRT=0x02 /
+ * _GENERIC_RMV=0x01).  These are the durable in-tree primitives used by
+ * the VLAN and MPLS push/pop encoders.
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OP_GENERIC_INSRT	0x02u
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OP_GENERIC_RMV	0x01u
+
+/* Generic INSRT/RMV operand layout: bits[7:0]=offset, bits[15:8]=size.
+ * Cross-ref SDK fm_manip.h HMCD_{INSRT,RMV}_{OFFSET,SIZE}_SHIFT.
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMCD_INSRT_OFFSET_SHIFT	0
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMCD_INSRT_SIZE_SHIFT	8
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMCD_RMV_OFFSET_SHIFT	0
+#define FMAN_PCD_HMCD_RMV_SIZE_SHIFT	8
+
+/*
+ * Frame-relative byte offsets where the VLAN / MPLS shim is
+ * inserted/removed.  A VLAN tag sits right after the 12-byte Ethernet
+ * dst+src MAC pair, before the EtherType.  An MPLS label sits after the
+ * EtherType (the MANIP node is used on MPLS-over-Ethernet frames whose
+ * EtherType is 0x8847/0x8848, so the label stack begins at offset 14).
+ * RM 8.7.5 + cross-ref SDK fm_manip.c BuildHmct e_FM_PCD_MANIP_*_GENERIC.
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_VLAN_TAG_OFFSET	12u
+#define FMAN_PCD_VLAN_TAG_SIZE	4u
+#define FMAN_PCD_MPLS_LABEL_OFFSET	14u
+#define FMAN_PCD_MPLS_LABEL_SIZE	4u
+
+/* VLAN TCI field packing (host-side helpers; the assembled 32-bit
+ * command payload is written big-endian by iowrite32be).
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_VLAN_PCP_SHIFT	13
+#define FMAN_PCD_VLAN_VID_MASK	0x0fffu
+
+/* MPLS label-entry field packing per RFC 3032 (label[31:12], tc[11:9],
+ * s[8], ttl[7:0]).
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_MPLS_LABEL_SHIFT	12
+#define FMAN_PCD_MPLS_TC_SHIFT	9
+#define FMAN_PCD_MPLS_S_SHIFT	8
+#define FMAN_PCD_MPLS_LABEL_MASK	0x000fffffu
+
+/**
+ * struct fman_pcd_hm_node - one MURAM-resident header-manip template.
+ * @node:     anchor on pcd->manip_list (protected by pcd->lock)
+ * @pcd:      owning PCD subsystem; back-pointer for MURAM free
+ * @port_id:  the FMan port this node was installed for (bookkeeping)
+ * @hmtd_off: MURAM byte offset of the 16-byte HMTD record (the value
+ *            returned to the caller as the opaque handle, and carried
+ *            by a CC action's hm_handle per spec sec 5.4)
+ * @hmtd:     CPU-visible iomem pointer to the HMTD
+ * @hmct_off: MURAM byte offset of the HMCT command-table region
+ * @hmct:     CPU-visible iomem pointer to the HMCT
+ * @hmct_sz:  bytes allocated for @hmct
+ * @lock:     per-node spinlock guarding the encoder writes
+ *
+ * Definition is private to this translation unit.
+ */
+struct fman_pcd_hm_node {
+	struct list_head	node;
+	struct fman_pcd	*pcd;
+	u8			port_id;
+	unsigned long		hmtd_off;
+	void __iomem		*hmtd;
+	unsigned long		hmct_off;
+	void __iomem		*hmct;
+	size_t			hmct_sz;
+	spinlock_t		lock;
+};
+
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+/* Per-op HMCT encoders - RM 8.7.5                                     */
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+
+/*
+ * Each encoder writes its command word(s) and optional inline payload
+ * starting at @cur, and returns the iomem address just past the bytes
+ * it wrote (so the dispatch loop can chain ops), writing the iomem
+ * address of the FIRST 32-bit word of the LAST command it emitted into
+ * *last_cmd (so the caller can OR HMCD_LAST into it once after all ops
+ * are emitted - matches SDK fm_manip.c BuildHmct() lines 1074-1076).
+ */
+
+static void __iomem *
+hm_encode_vlan_insert(const struct fman_pcd_hm_hw_op *op,
+		      void __iomem *cur, void __iomem **last_cmd)
+{
+	u32 cmd;
+	u32 payload;
+
+	/* Generic insert at L2 offset 12 (after the 12-byte src+dst MAC
+	 * pair, before the EtherType), size 4 bytes carrying inline
+	 * TPID(2)+TCI(2).  RM 8.7.5 generic INSRT + cross-ref SDK
+	 * fm_manip.c BuildHmct e_FM_PCD_MANIP_INSRT_GENERIC (line 532).
+	 */
+	cmd  = (u32)FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OP_GENERIC_INSRT << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OC_SHIFT;
+	cmd |= (u32)FMAN_PCD_VLAN_TAG_OFFSET << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_INSRT_OFFSET_SHIFT;
+	cmd |= (u32)FMAN_PCD_VLAN_TAG_SIZE << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_INSRT_SIZE_SHIFT;
+
+	iowrite32be(cmd, cur);
+	*last_cmd = cur;
+	cur += 4;
+
+	/* Inline payload: TPID in high 16 bits, then the TCI (PCP[15:13]
+	 * | VID[11:0]) in the low 16 bits.  The neutral hw-op fields are
+	 * already FMan big-endian-ready host values; iowrite32be does the
+	 * host->BE swap on the assembled word.
+	 */
+	payload  = (u32)op->vlan_insert.tpid_be << 16;
+	payload |= ((u32)(op->vlan_insert.pcp & 0x7) << FMAN_PCD_VLAN_PCP_SHIFT);
+	payload |= (u32)(op->vlan_insert.vid & FMAN_PCD_VLAN_VID_MASK);
+	iowrite32be(payload, cur);
+	cur += 4;
+
+	return cur;
+}
+
+static void __iomem *
+hm_encode_vlan_strip(void __iomem *cur, void __iomem **last_cmd)
+{
+	u32 cmd;
+
+	/* Generic remove at L2 offset 12, size 4 bytes (drop one VLAN
+	 * tag).  Cross-ref SDK fm_manip.c BuildHmct
+	 * e_FM_PCD_MANIP_RMV_GENERIC (line 442).
+	 */
+	cmd  = (u32)FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OP_GENERIC_RMV << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OC_SHIFT;
+	cmd |= (u32)FMAN_PCD_VLAN_TAG_OFFSET << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_RMV_OFFSET_SHIFT;
+	cmd |= (u32)FMAN_PCD_VLAN_TAG_SIZE << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_RMV_SIZE_SHIFT;
+
+	iowrite32be(cmd, cur);
+	*last_cmd = cur;
+	cur += 4;
+
+	return cur;
+}
+
+static void __iomem *
+hm_encode_mpls_push(const struct fman_pcd_hm_hw_op *op,
+		    void __iomem *cur, void __iomem **last_cmd)
+{
+	u32 cmd;
+	u32 label_entry;
+
+	/* Generic insert at offset 14 (after the EtherType), size 4 bytes
+	 * carrying the inline 32-bit MPLS label entry.  RM 8.7.5 generic
+	 * INSRT + RFC 3032 label-entry layout.
+	 */
+	cmd  = (u32)FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OP_GENERIC_INSRT << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OC_SHIFT;
+	cmd |= (u32)FMAN_PCD_MPLS_LABEL_OFFSET << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_INSRT_OFFSET_SHIFT;
+	cmd |= (u32)FMAN_PCD_MPLS_LABEL_SIZE << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_INSRT_SIZE_SHIFT;
+
+	iowrite32be(cmd, cur);
+	*last_cmd = cur;
+	cur += 4;
+
+	/* MPLS label entry (RFC 3032): label[31:12] | tc[11:9] | s[8] |
+	 * ttl[7:0].  Assembled in host order, written big-endian.
+	 */
+	label_entry  = (op->mpls_push.label & FMAN_PCD_MPLS_LABEL_MASK)
+		<< FMAN_PCD_MPLS_LABEL_SHIFT;
+	label_entry |= ((u32)(op->mpls_push.tc & 0x7) << FMAN_PCD_MPLS_TC_SHIFT);
+	label_entry |= ((u32)(op->mpls_push.s & 0x1) << FMAN_PCD_MPLS_S_SHIFT);
+	label_entry |= (u32)op->mpls_push.ttl;
+	iowrite32be(label_entry, cur);
+	cur += 4;
+
+	return cur;
+}
+
+static void __iomem *
+hm_encode_mpls_pop(void __iomem *cur, void __iomem **last_cmd)
+{
+	u32 cmd;
+
+	/* Generic remove at offset 14, size 4 bytes (pop one label). */
+	cmd  = (u32)FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OP_GENERIC_RMV << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_OC_SHIFT;
+	cmd |= (u32)FMAN_PCD_MPLS_LABEL_OFFSET << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_RMV_OFFSET_SHIFT;
+	cmd |= (u32)FMAN_PCD_MPLS_LABEL_SIZE << FMAN_PCD_HMCD_RMV_SIZE_SHIFT;
+
+	iowrite32be(cmd, cur);
+	*last_cmd = cur;
+	cur += 4;
+
+	return cur;
+}
+
+/**
+ * fman_pcd_hm_install() - program one ordered-op-list HM node.
+ * @pcd:     the PCD subsystem (from fman_get_pcd())
+ * @port_id: the FMan port the node is installed for
+ * @spec:    neutral, big-endian-ready op list (host->BE done by caller)
+ * @handle:  on success, receives the HMTD MURAM byte offset (the opaque
+ *           handle the caller passes to fman_pcd_hm_destroy() and that a
+ *           CC action carries as hm_handle)
+ *
+ * Return: 0 on success (writes @handle); negative errno on failure.
+ *
+ * RM 8.7.5 (HMTD/HMCT layout) + RM 8.7.5.4 + cross-ref SDK fm_manip.c
+ * FmPcdManipCreate() / BuildHmct().
+ */
+int fman_pcd_hm_install(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 port_id,
+			const struct fman_pcd_hm_hw_spec *spec, u32 *handle)
+{
+	struct fman_pcd_hm_node *hm;
+	struct muram_info *muram;
+	struct mutex *pcd_lock;
+	void __iomem *last_cmd = NULL;
+	void __iomem *cur;
+	void __iomem *end;
+	unsigned long off;
+	unsigned long flags;
+	void __iomem *vb;
+	u32 last_word;
+	u16 cfg;
+	long err;
+	u8 i;
+
+	if (!pcd || !spec || !handle)
+		return -EINVAL;
+	if (spec->num_ops == 0 || spec->num_ops > FMAN_PCD_HM_HW_MAX_OPS)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	muram = fman_get_muram(fman_pcd_get_fman(pcd));
+	if (!muram)
+		return -ENXIO;
+
+	hm = kzalloc(sizeof(*hm), GFP_KERNEL);
+	if (!hm)
+		return -ENOMEM;
+
+	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&hm->node);
+	spin_lock_init(&hm->lock);
+	hm->pcd = pcd;
+	hm->port_id = port_id;
+
+	/* HMTD: 16-byte MURAM-resident descriptor, zero-initialised so
+	 * opCode=0 (no manip) until we finalise below.
+	 */
+	off = fman_pcd_muram_alloc(pcd, FMAN_PCD_HMTD_SIZE);
+	if (IS_ERR_VALUE(off)) {
+		err = (long)off;
+		kfree(hm);
+		return (int)err;
+	}
+	vb = (void __iomem *)fman_muram_offset_to_vbase(muram, off);
+	if (!vb) {
+		fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, off, FMAN_PCD_HMTD_SIZE);
+		kfree(hm);
+		return -ENXIO;
+	}
+	hm->hmtd_off = off;
+	hm->hmtd = vb;
+	memset_io(vb, 0, FMAN_PCD_HMTD_SIZE);
+
+	/* HMCT: command-table scratch, zeroed so any unused slack stays
+	 * inactive (silicon never walks past the HMCD_LAST-marked word).
+	 */
+	off = fman_pcd_muram_alloc(pcd, FMAN_PCD_HMCT_SIZE);
+	if (IS_ERR_VALUE(off)) {
+		err = (long)off;
+		fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, hm->hmtd_off, FMAN_PCD_HMTD_SIZE);
+		kfree(hm);
+		return (int)err;
+	}
+	vb = (void __iomem *)fman_muram_offset_to_vbase(muram, off);
+	if (!vb) {
+		fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, off, FMAN_PCD_HMCT_SIZE);
+		fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, hm->hmtd_off, FMAN_PCD_HMTD_SIZE);
+		kfree(hm);
+		return -ENXIO;
+	}
+	hm->hmct_off = off;
+	hm->hmct = vb;
+	hm->hmct_sz = FMAN_PCD_HMCT_SIZE;
+	memset_io(vb, 0, FMAN_PCD_HMCT_SIZE);
+
+	/* Encoder dispatch under node->lock.  spin_lock_irqsave matches
+	 * the public-ABI softirq-safe promise for future runtime updates.
+	 */
+	spin_lock_irqsave(&hm->lock, flags);
+
+	cur = hm->hmct;
+	end = hm->hmct + hm->hmct_sz;
+
+	for (i = 0; i < spec->num_ops; i++) {
+		const struct fman_pcd_hm_hw_op *op = &spec->ops[i];
+
+		/* Worst-case op is INSRT command word + 4-byte payload = 8
+		 * bytes; bounds-check before dispatch.
+		 */
+		if (cur + 8 > end) {
+			spin_unlock_irqrestore(&hm->lock, flags);
+			goto err_free_hmct;
+		}
+
+		switch (op->type) {
+		case FMAN_PCD_HM_HW_OP_VLAN_STRIP:
+			cur = hm_encode_vlan_strip(cur, &last_cmd);
+			break;
+		case FMAN_PCD_HM_HW_OP_VLAN_INSERT:
+			cur = hm_encode_vlan_insert(op, cur, &last_cmd);
+			break;
+		case FMAN_PCD_HM_HW_OP_MPLS_PUSH:
+			cur = hm_encode_mpls_push(op, cur, &last_cmd);
+			break;
+		case FMAN_PCD_HM_HW_OP_MPLS_POP:
+			cur = hm_encode_mpls_pop(cur, &last_cmd);
+			break;
+		default:
+			spin_unlock_irqrestore(&hm->lock, flags);
+			goto err_free_hmct;
+		}
+	}
+
+	if (!last_cmd) {
+		spin_unlock_irqrestore(&hm->lock, flags);
+		goto err_free_hmct;
+	}
+
+	/* Stamp HMCD_LAST onto the last command word so the silicon walker
+	 * terminates (SDK fm_manip.c lines 1074-1076).
+	 */
+	last_word = ioread32be(last_cmd);
+	iowrite32be(last_word | FMAN_PCD_HMCD_LAST, last_cmd);
+
+	/* Finalise the HMTD: cfg(TYPE|EXT_HMCT) then hmcdBasePtr then
+	 * opCode (SDK fm_manip.c lines 1223-1230 order).
+	 */
+	cfg = FMAN_PCD_HMTD_CFG_TYPE | FMAN_PCD_HMTD_CFG_EXT_HMCT;
+	iowrite16be(cfg, hm->hmtd + FMAN_PCD_HMTD_OFF_CFG);
+	iowrite32be((u32)hm->hmct_off, hm->hmtd + FMAN_PCD_HMTD_OFF_HMCD_BASE);
+	iowrite8(FMAN_PCD_HMAN_OC, hm->hmtd + FMAN_PCD_HMTD_OFF_OPCODE);
+
+	spin_unlock_irqrestore(&hm->lock, flags);
+
+	/* Publish on the PCD manip list for unbind-time teardown. */
+	pcd_lock = fman_pcd_get_lock(pcd);
+	mutex_lock(pcd_lock);
+	list_add_tail(&hm->node, fman_pcd_get_manip_list(pcd));
+	mutex_unlock(pcd_lock);
+
+	*handle = (u32)hm->hmtd_off;
+	return 0;
+
+err_free_hmct:
+	fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, hm->hmct_off, hm->hmct_sz);
+	fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, hm->hmtd_off, FMAN_PCD_HMTD_SIZE);
+	kfree(hm);
+	return -EINVAL;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_hm_install);
+
+/**
+ * fman_pcd_hm_destroy() - tear down one HM node by handle.
+ * @pcd:     the PCD subsystem
+ * @port_id: the FMan port (matched against the node for safety)
+ * @handle:  the HMTD MURAM offset returned by fman_pcd_hm_install()
+ *
+ * Idempotent: a handle that matches no live node (already destroyed, or
+ * never installed) is a no-op returning 0.  Frees the HMCT then the HMTD
+ * MURAM regions and the node.
+ *
+ * RM 8.7.5 + cross-ref SDK fm_manip.c FmPcdManipDelete.
+ */
+int fman_pcd_hm_destroy(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 port_id, u32 handle)
+{
+	struct fman_pcd_hm_node *hm, *tmp;
+	struct fman_pcd_hm_node *found = NULL;
+	struct list_head *head;
+	struct mutex *pcd_lock;
+
+	if (!pcd || handle == 0)
+		return 0;
+
+	pcd_lock = fman_pcd_get_lock(pcd);
+	head = fman_pcd_get_manip_list(pcd);
+
+	mutex_lock(pcd_lock);
+	list_for_each_entry_safe(hm, tmp, head, node) {
+		if (hm->hmtd_off == (unsigned long)handle &&
+		    hm->port_id == port_id) {
+			list_del(&hm->node);
+			found = hm;
+			break;
+		}
+	}
+	mutex_unlock(pcd_lock);
+
+	if (!found)
+		return 0;
+
+	/* Zero the HMTD opCode first so silicon stops referencing the
+	 * HMCT before we free it (defensive; the CC action that pointed
+	 * here must already have been rewritten by the caller).
+	 */
+	iowrite8(0, found->hmtd + FMAN_PCD_HMTD_OFF_OPCODE);
+
+	fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, found->hmct_off, found->hmct_sz);
+	fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, found->hmtd_off, FMAN_PCD_HMTD_SIZE);
+	kfree(found);
+	return 0;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_hm_destroy);
